 (49,8,'_about_us_intro_intro_text','<p>When you feel ill you make an appointment to see a doctor. Some people even go to A&amp;E.</p>'),
 (50,8,'_about_us_intro_steps_title','The average waiting time to see a doctor in the UK can be over two weeks in some areas. And when your appointment date does come around, you can spend hours travelling and sitting in waiting rooms – hours that could be better spent with your family or at work. If you do decide to speed things up by going to A&E, you’re likely to wait all night to get a minor condition diagnosed by a doctor who has more serious situations to deal with.Although no online consultation can completely replace seeing a doctor in person, the ability to treat a patient over the internet can alleviate some of the pressure doctors are under. Using the latest video technology, we’ve turned weeks of waiting to see a doctor and long nights in A&E into a consultation whenever you want, wherever you are – all so you can get well sooner.'),
 (51,8,'_about_us_intro_step1_title','Quick'),
 (52,8,'_about_us_intro_step1_desc','We have hundreds of doctors waiting for you, so you can see a doctor within minutes or book an appointment 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.'),
