 (88,11,'_faq_patients_content','<h4>What is VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>VideoDoc is a website and mobile app that lets you see a doctor through a secure high quality video platform. This is a new way for you to see your own GP, or a doctor of your choice, when you really need to. It’s convenient for you as you can see a doctor in your home, while at work or on the move. It’s convenient for doctors as they can see patients at home or in between consultations at their surgery. No electronic system will completely replace the vital in-person work of Doctors. However, the ability to triage, treat, diagnose, prescribe and follow up with patients is possible using VideoDoc.</p>\r\n<h4>How much does an consultation cost?</h4>\r\n<p>A consultation with a GP is £22. You will be charged extra for additional services, such as a blood test or other diagnostic tests.</p>\r\n<h4>How do I get a referral if further investigation or treatment is needed?</h4>\r\n<p>If you need specialist attention, your GP will be able to refer you to the right kind of consultant for your condition as appropriate.</p>\r\n<h4>Can my dependant have a consultation?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. You can select a consultation for your dependant using your own account.</p>\r\n<h4>How do I get a prescription?</h4>\r\n<p>If your VideoDoc consultation results in a prescription, your VideoDoc can</p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n<li>Email or fax the prescription to you</li>\r\n<li>Email or fax the prescription to a pharmacy of your choice</li>\r\n<li>Arrange for the medicines to be delivered to you</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Is there an extra charge for a prescription?</h4>\r\n<p>Absolutely not we include the cost of the prescription in the price of the consultation.</p>\r\n<h4>What happens if I lose internet connection during my consultation?</h4>\r\n<p>We always recommend you make sure you have a stable internet connection and that your device is plugged in or charged before you consultation begins.</p>\r\n<h4>Will my consultation be recorded?</h4>\r\n<p>No. We value the privacy of both the patient and doctor so no consultations are recorded by video. The VideoDoc will make written notes during your consultations, if you are not seeing your own GP you can request these to be sent to your own GP.</p>\r\n<h4>Will my VideoDoc review my medical history before my consultation?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes – if you make it available to us. It isn’t necessary, but the more information you give the VideoDoc about previous conditions and treatments the quicker they can diagnose, prescribe and give medical advice tailored to your needs.</p>\r\n<h4>What’s your prescription policy?</h4>\r\n<p>Our doctors will write private prescriptions for a wide range of conditions when deemed medically appropriate.</p>\r\n<h4>What medical devices does VideoDoc support?</h4>\r\n<p>You can connect the following devices to your VideoDoc account:\r\n                    <br>\r\n                    <ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n                        <li>Bodymedia</li>\r\n                        <li>Fat Secret</li>\r\n                        <li>Dailymile</li>\r\n                        <li>Fitbit</li>\r\n                        <li>Fit bug</li>\r\n                        <li>Fleetly</li>\r\n                        <li>Garmin</li>\r\n                        <li>iHealth</li>\r\n                        <li>Jawbone</li>\r\n                        <li>LFconnectMoves</li>\r\n                        <li>Life Fitness</li>\r\n                        <li>ManageBGL</li>\r\n                        <li>MapMyFitness</li>\r\n                        <li>MapMyHike</li>\r\n                        <li>MapMyRide</li>\r\n                        <li>MapMyRun</li>\r\n                        <li>MapMyWalk</li>\r\n                        <li>Medisana</li>\r\n                        <li>Misfit</li>\r\n                        <li>Movable</li>\r\n                        <li>Nike+</li>\r\n                        <li>Omron</li>\r\n                        <li>RunKeeper</li>\r\n                        <li>Starve</li>\r\n                        <li>Sync</li>\r\n                        <li>Telcare Blood Glucose Monitoring System</li>\r\n                        <li>Withings </li>\r\n                    </ul></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>About our website</h3>\r\n<h4>Can I get technical support?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. We have a 24/7 support centre that can help you with any general VideoDoc technical issues. Most issues are fixed right away, but please be aware that others can take up to 24 hours.</p>\r\n<h4>Do you have a privacy policy?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. We take your privacy seriously. We comply with Ireland’s Data Protection Act and the US HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act). We only share your information with your chosen doctor but that’s only if you give us permission. You can read more about our privacy policy <a href=\"http://videodoc.co.uk/tandc/#privacy\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<h4>Are emails between us kept private?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. All emails between you and VideoDoc are encrypted and stored in a secure place.</p>\r\n<h4>How can I be sure my medical history is kept private?</h4>\r\n<p>We store all your information in state-of-the-art data centres with the most robust Tier 1 network cloud technology. We have several certifications that ensure the highest levels of security including an SAS-70 Type II Audit and a Microsoft Gold Certified Partnership.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>General and Enquiries</h4>\r\n<p>If you have a question not answered here, feel free to get in touch <a href=\"mailto:info@videodoc.ie\">info@videodoc.ie or call us on 01 555 5451.</a></p>'),
 (89,11,'_faq_doctors_content','<h3>About our service</h3>\r\n<p>Thinking of offering a VideoDoc service? Here are the answers to the questions on most doctor’s minds. If you want to know something about us that’s not covered here, just <a href=\"mailto:doctor@videodoc.ie\">ask</a></p>\r\n<h4>What is VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>No electronic system will completely replace the vital in-person work of doctors. However, the ability to triage, treat, diagnose, prescribe and follow up with patients in a virtual environment alleviates some resource burden. It also provides the utmost in convenience for patients.</p>\r\n<h4>How do I sign up to VideoDoctor?</h4>\r\n<p>Becoming a VideoDoctor couldn’t be easier. <a href=\"mailto:doctor@videodoc.ie\">Contact us now</a> to relearn more or to register as a VideoDoc to offer this great service to your patients. </p>\r\n<h4>Does VideoDoc work with the NHS?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes, VideoDoc offers NHS CCG or Foundation Trust, a GP practice free telemedicine tools. Just contact nhs@videodoc.co.uk to find out how we can help you to see NHS patients online today.</p>\r\n<h4>Can I hold consultations with children on VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. Every consultation with a dependant is flagged on our patient tracking board letting you know in advance that the consultation is with a minor.</p>\r\n<h4>What do I need to become a VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>You’ll need a webcam, microphone and internet connection. The VideoDoc registration team will provide you with login details once your account has been verified.</p>\r\n<p>VideoDoc supports the following operating systems:</p>\r\n<p><br /> <b>Windows</b> <br />Internet Explorer 10 or later (32-bit mode with OpenTok plug-in compatibility) <br />Chrome (latest) <br />Firefox (latest) <br /><br /> <b>Mac</b> <br />Chrome (latest) <br />Firefox (latest) <br /><br /> iOS-based smart device <br />iOS 7 or later <br /><br />Android-based smart device<Br>KitKat Android 4.4 or later.</p>\r\n<h4>How do I know if a patient is already receiving treatment?</h4>\r\n<p>We ask patients to tell us about any prior treatment and we keep a record of all VideoDoc consultations and prescriptions issued. You can view your patient’s medical record and past consultations when you’re conducting their VideoDoc consultation.</p>\r\n<h4>Can I prescribe medication?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. You can prescribe medicines. All prescriptions are handled in the normal way in accordance with IMC remote prescribing guidelines.</p>\r\n<h4>Are discharge instructions included at the end of a VideoDoc consultation?</h4>\r\n<p>VideoDoc provides clinical documentation on discharge which are emailed directly to patients.This information is emailed directly to the patient based on information selected from the VideoDoc platform.</p>\r\n<h4>Will my VideoDoc consultation be recorded?</h4>\r\n<p>No. VideoDoc respects the privacy of every patient-doctor consultation and we do not record consultations.</p>\r\n<h4>Is VideoDoc secure?</h4>\r\n<p>We take security and privacy very seriously. We comply with Ireland’s Data Protection Act and the US standards: HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act). Please read more about Security and Privacy in our Terms and Conditions.</p>\r\n<h4>Is VideoDoc registered with the Care Quality Commission?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes, VideoDoc is a registered service with the Care Quality Commission (hyper link to CQC website where videodoc registration will be)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>General and Enquiries</h4>\r\n<p>If you have any questions, please get in touch at <a href=\"mailto:info@videodoc.ie\">info@videodoc.ie or call us on 01 555 5451.</a></p>'),
