 (167,85,'_doctors_faqs_content','<h3>About our service</h3>\r\n<p>Thinking of becoming one of our doctors? Here are the answers to the questions on most doctor’s minds. If you want to know something about us that’s not covered here, just <a href=\"mailto:doctor@videodoc.co.uk\">ask</a></p>\r\n<h4>What is VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>VideoDoc is a web portal and mobile application that lets you treat a patient through a secure high quality clinical platform. It’s convenient for you as you can consult with your patients from your home, while at the surgery or on the move.</p>\r\n<h4>How do I sign up to VideoDoctor?</h4>\r\n<p>Becoming a VideoDoctor couldn’t be easier. <a href=\"mailto:doctor@videodoc.co.uk\">Contact us now</a> and a Healthcare Liaison Associate will give you a call or email you to begin the registration process. We are offering all IMC registered GPs the opportunity to becomea  VideoDoc and use our telemedicine tool in their own practice – or as a way to expand patient reach and create an additional revenue stream.</p>\r\n<h4>What conditions does VideoDoc offer treatment for?</h4>\r\n<p>You can diagnose and treat most everyday physical, mental, behavioural and emotional conditions, a small selection includes: <br /><br /><b>Most common</b></p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n<li>Upper respiratory infection</li>\r\n<li>Cold</li>\r\n<li>Cough</li>\r\n<li>Influenza</li>\r\n<li>Nasal congestion</li>\r\n<li>Allergies</li>\r\n<li>Fever</li>\r\n<li>Athlete\'s foot</li>\r\n<li>Sports injuries</li>\r\n<li>Rolled ankle</li>\r\n<li>Travel medicine</li>\r\n<li>Erectile dysfunction</li>\r\n<li>Acne</li>\r\n<li>Oral contraception</li>\r\n<li>Weight loss</li>\r\n<li>STIs</li>\r\n<li>Cholesterol</li>\r\n<li>Stress</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><br /><b>Most irritating</b></p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n<li>Bladder infections</li>\r\n<li>Cellulitis</li>\r\n<li>Fever</li>\r\n<li>Eye irritation</li>\r\n<li>Asthma (stable, non-urgent)</li>\r\n<li>Yeast infection</li>\r\n<li>Nausea</li>\r\n<li>Back pain</li>\r\n<li>Skin infection</li>\r\n<li>Dermatitis</li>\r\n<li>Heartburn – Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease (GERD)</li>\r\n<li>Dry skin – eczema</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><br /><b>Most inconvenient </b></p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n<li>Rash</li>\r\n<li>Pink eye</li>\r\n<li>Genital lesions</li>\r\n<li>Depression</li>\r\n<li>Diarrhoea</li>\r\n<li>Dry scalp</li>\r\n<li>Hay fever</li>\r\n<li>Lice</li>\r\n<li>Poison oak / poison ivy</li>\r\n<li>Scabies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><br /><b>VideoDoc can also healthcare professionals and therapists to help with </b></p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n<li>ADHD</li>\r\n<li>Alcohol abuse</li>\r\n<li>Anger management</li>\r\n<li>Anxiety</li>\r\n<li>Behavioural issues</li>\r\n<li>Bi-polar disorder</li>\r\n<li>Changes in mood</li>\r\n<li>Chronic pain</li>\r\n<li>Co-dependency</li>\r\n<li>Depression</li>\r\n<li>Drug abuse</li>\r\n<li>Eating disorders</li>\r\n<li>Grief</li>\r\n<li>Impulsivity</li>\r\n<li>Life stresses</li>\r\n<li>Loss</li>\r\n<li>Obsessive Compulsive Disorder (OCD)</li>\r\n<li>Panic</li>\r\n<li>Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)</li>\r\n<li>Relationship issues</li>\r\n<li>Self-esteem</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Can I hold appointments with children on VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. But we ask every patient under 16 to be accompanied by a parent, guardian or teacher. Every appointment with a dependant is flagged on our patient tracking board letting you know in advance that the appointment is with a minor.</p>\r\n<h4> </h4>\r\n<h4>Can I handle emergency situations on VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>No. You cannot treat serious medical conditions on VideoDoc. Examples include:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n<li>Chest pain or pressure</li>\r\n<li>Significant, uncontrolled bleeding</li>\r\n<li>Difficulty in breathing</li>\r\n<li>Unconsciousness</li>\r\n<li>Poisoning</li>\r\n<li>Moderate to severe burns</li>\r\n<li>Convulsions or seizures</li>\r\n<li>Serious head, neck or back injuries</li>\r\n<li>Serious limb impairments or broken bones</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In these cases, patients must seek urgent medical help.</p>\r\n<h4>What do I need to become a VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>You’ll need a webcam, microphone and internet connection. Our Healthcare Liaison Associate will give you your login details once they’ve verified your account.</p>\r\n<p><br /> <b>Windows</b> <br />Internet Explorer 10 or later (32-bit mode with OpenTok plug-in compatibility) <br />Chrome (latest) <br />Firefox (latest) <br /><br /> <b>Mac</b> <br />Chrome (latest) <br />Firefox (latest) <br /><br /> iOS-based smart device <br />iOS 7 or later <br /><br />Android-based smart device <br />KitKat Android 4.4 or later</p>\r\n<h4>Where is VideoDoc available?</h4>\r\n<p>You can access VideoDoc from virtually anywhere, such as your home, practice, on the move, even abroad. You can see patients at a location that suits you.</p>\r\n<h4>Is VideoDoc easy to use?</h4>\r\n<p>Yes. Our user interface has been expertly designed so patients and doctors can easily attend an appointment through any type of computer or mobile device.</p>\r\n<h4>When can I become a VideoDoct?</h4>\r\n<p>Now. Simply sign up <a href=\"sign-up.aspx\">here</a>. Once you’ve filled out the online form our team will confirm your registration within 24 hours (Monday to Friday). We’ll then send you a VideoDoc training pack and from there you’ll become an approved VideoDoc.</p>\r\n<h4> </h4>\r\n<h4>When do you advise a patient to use VideoDoc?</h4>\r\n<p>70% of visits to A&amp;E are considered unnecessary or preventable. While medical care may be needed, the travel, time away from work, long waits and cost of the visit can be avoided. VideoDoc is an excellent option for people who</p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullets\">\r\n<li>Are considering A&amp;E for a non-emergency condition</li>\r\n<li>Need a new prescription or refill</li>\r\n<li>Are travelling and need medical care</li>\r\n<li>Want a second opinion</li>\r\n<li>Want to talk directly to a specialist</li>\r\n<li>Need referral to a specialist</li>\r\n<li>Don’t feel comfortable seeing their own GP about a specific issue</li>\r\n<li>Need medical care outside practice hours, such as nights, weekends or holidays</li>\r\n<li>Need a medical question quickly answered</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4> </h4>\r\n<h4> </h4>\r\n<h4> </h4>\r\n<h4>VideoDoc consultations can be initiated using a PC</h4>\r\n<p>VideoDoc enables consultations with a PC, providing a robust, secure, and encrypted communications solution worldwide. VideoDoc ensures VideoVisits remain private. Our video conferencing technology identifies the device and initiates a secure, end-to-end video connection. Our video technology is based on latest WebRTC protocol, ensuring a high-quality user experience.</p>\r\n<h4>VideoDoc consultations can be initiated using a mobile device (iOS, Android)</h4>\r\n<p>VideoDoc enables conferencing via mobile device. Our solution delivers high performance, encrypted video consultations between wireless devices and/or PCs. Our video conferencing solution ensures a high quality user experience by utilising best practice protocols that optimise encrypted real-time content over low-bandwidth networks. Currently, VideoDoc supports 96% of smartphones* sold in the marketplace, including iOS and Android mobile operating systems.</p>\r\n<h4>Are discharge instructions included at the end of a VideoDoc consultation?</h4>\r\n<p>VideoDoc provides clinical documentation at the end of most VideoVisits. This information is emailed directly to the patient based on information selected from the VideoDoc platform.</p>\r\n<h4>What happens if my Wi-Fi drops or device cuts off during a VideoDoc consultation?</h4>\r\n<p>If you log back in within five minutes we’ll reconnect you with your patient. If you cannot connect prior to this we’ll offer the patient an alternative appointment with you at another time, an appointment with a doctor available at that time, or a refund.</p>\r\n<h4>Will my VideoDoc consultation be recorded?</h4>\r\n<p>No. VideoDoc will maintain a complete written record but there are no recordings of the consultations.</p>\r\n<h4> </h4>\r\n<h4>Is VideoDoc secure?</h4>\r\n<p>We take security and privacy very seriously. We comply with the Data Protection Act and the US standards: HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) and will only share information with patients selected doctors and pharmacist if they say we can. Please read more about Security and Privacy in our Security and Privacy Policy.</p>\r\n<h4> </h4>'),
