 (265,8,'_about_us_clinical_team_members','a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Dr. Robert Kelly\";s:4:\"post\";s:31:\"MD MBA, FRCPI, Medical Director\";s:8:\"photo_id\";i:118;s:5:\"photo\";s:69:\"http://videodoc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/team1.jpg\";s:4:\"desc\";s:659:\"<p>Interventional cardiologist, digital healthcare innovator and entrepreneur, Dr. Kelly’s passion is finding innovative ways to make healthcare better. This includes connected health, telemedicine and the use of mobile technology. His special interests cover cardiovascular imaging, stunting, risk assessment, cardiac monitoring and digital healthcare innovation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Kelly completed his cardiology training in Ireland, the UK and the USA. He’s registered with the Irish Medical Council and General Medical Council in the UK.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Kelly is an RCSI graduate and holds an MBA from Henley Management College.</p>\";}}'),
 (266,8,'_about_us_advisors_advisors','a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Mark Kelly\";s:4:\"post\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"photo_id\";i:120;s:5:\"photo\";s:68:\"http://videodoc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/mark.jpg\";s:4:\"desc\";s:1361:\"<p>Managing Director &amp; Partner with H.I.G. Capital.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mark Kelly currently heads H.I.G.\'s LBO fund in Chicago. Joining in 2007 as a founding partner of H.I.G. Europe and has been responsible for all aspects of the investment process across multiple sectors, most notably Healthcare, Consumer and Business Services. H.I.G. is a global mid-market private equity firm with more than $19 billion of capital under management. H.I.G. is a global mid-market private equity firm with more than $19 billion of capital under management. H.I.G. specialises in acquiring controlling stakes in medium sized companies with attractive growth potential and distressed turnaround situations. H.I.G.\'s companies have combined worldwide sales in excess of $30 billion.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Prior to H.I.G., Mark was Chief Operations Officer of Europe\'s largest foodservice company Brakes Group (€3bn), and CEO of Pauley\'s Foods. Previously, he was with Merrill Lynch (Hg) Capital and Bain &amp; Company\'s private equity group in San Francisco and London. Prior to that, Mark ran the manufacturing operations of a subsidiary of the Jefferson Smurfit Group plc., now Smurfit Kappa</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"> </p>\r\n<p>Mark holds BSc (Hons.) and an MA from Trinity College Dublin &amp; an MBA from Harvard.</p>\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"James Hummer\";s:4:\"post\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"photo_id\";i:119;s:5:\"photo\";s:70:\"http://videodoc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/hummer.jpg\";s:4:\"desc\";s:1346:\"<p>Managing Partner, Redrock Ventures. President, Luxemburg Capital</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Jim Hummer founded and led Whole Health Management, an innovative provider of direct contract, work-site employee health services to Fortune 500 companies, until it was merged into Walgreen Company in May of 2008. Upon the sale of Whole Health, Jim founded Luxemburg Capital, his family investment firm, and Redrock Ventures, his personal investment firm. He serves as Chairman of the Board for Endotronix and is a board member or advisor to several healthcare companies. Before Whole Health, Jim co-founded and was President of the Ivy Medical Group, a pioneer in the urgent care field. Previously, he was Director of Planning and Human Resources at Martin Marietta Corporation’s Chemical Group. Earlier, Jim was with Deloitte &amp; Touché, San Francisco, where he obtained his CPA. Jim has served on the Harvard Business School Alumni Board, the HBS Healthcare Alumni Association Board and currently serves on the Harvard University Healthcare Initiative Advisory Board, the Harvard School of Public Health Executive Leadership Council, the Qualcomm Life Advisory Board, and the Nanovic Institute Board at the University of Notre Dame.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Jim holds a BA in accounting from the University of Notre Dame and an MBA from Harvard.</p>\";}i:2;a:4:{s:4:\"name\";s:11:\"Mary Harney\";s:8:\"photo_id\";i:215;s:5:\"photo\";s:71:\"http://videodoc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/marks.png\";s:4:\"desc\";s:1268:\"<p>Former politician &amp; government minister.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mary Harney was a senior government minister in Ireland. With an entire political life characterised by a passion for reform, innovation and enterprise. After 17 years in government, Mary had reached the height of her career. She served as Tanaiste (Deputy Prime Minister) for 9 years, becoming the first woman to lead a political party in Ireland and holding many important ministerial portfolios. For seven years she had responsibility for Industrial Development and the promotion of Irish business in export markets. She established Science Foundation Ireland to strengthen Ireland\'s research capacity. She was Minister for Health &amp; Children for almost seven years and initiated major reforms including cancer services, in-care of the elderly and in the regulation of health professionals. She was also notably the longest serving female TD (Member of Parliament) in the state\'s history.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"> </p>\r\n<p>Mary has a deep knowledge of the interactions between business and government at National and European levels.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"> </p>\r\n<p>Mary is an Economics graduate from Trinity College Dublin and is now focusing on business having retired from politics in 2011.</p>\";}}'),
