 (81,1,'2015-11-15 12:47:19','2015-11-15 12:47:19','The finalists in the SFA National Small Business Awards 2016 have been officially announced by AJ Noonan, SFA Chairman and Chair of the Awards Judging Panel. The aim of the awards is to celebrate the achievements of business in Ireland, and to recognise the vital contribution of the small business sector to Irish industry.\r\n\r\nAn Taoiseach Enda Kenny, TD, who is Patron of the Awards, stated that: “As a passionate supporter of small firms I, on behalf of the Government, am delighted to support the SFA Awards. Small firms support the vast majority of jobs in all parts of our country and are leading our recovery. The Awards provide an opportunity to highlight the success of our small firms as they support our recovery by seeking out new markets and new opportunities. Supporting our small firms is essential to the Government’s strategy of securing the recovery and spreading it to every part of the country.” \r\n\r\nThe Awards prize package for VideoDoc includes an exhibition stand at that SFA National Small Business Showcase in February 2016, a strategic management masterclass weekend, a voucher for a Skillnets Management Works management team/CEO course, as well as broad-ranging national and local media coverage, valued at €50,000. \r\n\r\n','VideoDoc is recognised as one of the \"Best Emerging New Businesses\" in Ireland','','publish','open','open','','videodocs-mobile-app-reinvents-on-dmeand-healthcare','','','2016-01-31 09:50:42','2016-01-31 09:50:42','',0,'http://videodoc.co.uk/?p=81',0,'post','',0);
