 (234,2,'2016-09-26 15:41:54','2016-09-26 15:41:54','VideoDoc has joined the Applied Research for Connect Health (ARCH). Societal and demographic changes and associated economic drivers are forcing us to change the way we organise health and social care models. Leveraging technological development provides us with effective solutions in this regard and in many instances these have already been deployed in care settings with demonstrated effect. The challenge in Connected Health lies in a fundamental change in the construct and financing of the patient care model and in the regulatory frameworks that underpin it. To solve the multi-faceted Connected Health challenge specialised value chains need to be pulled together into networked solutions that are modular in their set-up, customizable in deployment and that deliver sustainable value to each individual firm as well as to the payer. This consortium proposes a flexible and modular home and community test-bed infrastructure, that will enable Irish industry to collaborate in order to evaluate how their component technologies can be used together to bring about more efficient care pathways.\r\n\r\n“We’re thrilled about joining ARCH and looking forward to contributing to the growth and sustainability of this innovative programme,” said VideoDoc CEO Damian Kissane.\r\n\r\nAs an ARCH member, VideoDoc will take on a greater role in shaping the future of telehealth technology, by collaborating with mHealth experts, accessing consultation and support from ARCH partners and voicing patients’ and doctors’ needs to policymakers through association initiatives. By joining ARCH VideoDoc has reinforced its commitment to telehealth in Ireland.\r\n\r\n<strong>About VideoDoc</strong>\r\nVideoDoc is an innovative telehealth software company with the mission to help people get well sooner. The VideoDoc platform allows healthcare providers to connect and treat their patients remotely, through a secure, video platform. VideoDoc is a web portal and mobile application tool which allows healthcare providers provide treatment anytime, anywhere, on any device. This is a new way for patients to conveniently see their own doctor face to face, online and get a prescription. Both the patient and doctor can be in their own home, office, surgery or even on the move The VideoDoc telemedicine platform is intuitive, requires minimal training, and sets itself apart with a unique tracking board feature and integration of clinical.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Applied Research for Connected Health (ARCH)</strong>\r\nARCH is the industry-driven technology centre for connected health research in Ireland. We provide access to world class clinicians, academics and patient cohorts to explore and evaluate potential connected health solutions for the global market. Ireland is in a unique position to become a global centre of activity and excellence in connected health. ARCH is at the centre of an unparalleled connected health education and research infrastructure that spans a range of activities from gathering, analysing and interpreting data, through the development of new knowledge and care models to implementing and evaluating change. ARCH adds value to R&amp;D, creating and retaining jobs.','VideoDoc joins Applied Research for Connection Health (ARCH)','','publish','open','open','','videodoc-joins-applied-research-for-connection-health-arch','','','2016-09-26 15:42:31','2016-09-26 15:42:31','',0,'http://videodoc.co.uk/?p=234',0,'post','',0),
